fees.description: Dishonoured Payment fee of $9.50 (inc GST) may apply to payments we attempt that are subsequently declined.
A $66.00 (inc GST) fee may apply each time we request to energise a property, or if you require a meter reading for any purpose.
A $66.00 (inc GST) fee may apply each time we request to de-energise a property, or if you require a meter reading for any purpose.
A $88.00 (inc GST) fee may apply each time you request a reconnection after disconnection for non-payment.

electricityContract.terms: See our Standing terms and conditions at www.dodo.com/energy/terms-prices-and-regulatory-information.
electricityContract.variation: We may vary these prices no more than once every 6 months, and provide you notice of any changes at least 5 business days before the change is effective. We will publish variations on our website and in a newspaper at least 10 business days prior.

timeOfUseRates.description: 7am to 1pm and 8pm to 10pm AEST business days

singleRate.description: Usually for a 16 hour period daily, including at least 6 hours between 8pm - 7am and at least 4 hours between 7am - 5pm

solarFeedInTariff.description: Retailer Feed-in Tariff (net & gross) - This plan is available to eligible small solar customers with a maximum 10kW panel size and an inverter system no greater than 10kW as part of an ongoing contract.

electricityContract.onExpiryDescription: Standing contracts do not expire until you notify us in accordance with our Standing Contract Terms and Conditions.
electricityContract.additionalFeeInformation: For further details on the information and fees presented, or the terms and conditions of the contract, please visit www.dodo.com/energy/terms-prices-and-regulatory-information or contact us on 13 dodo (13 36 36).
